definitions.definition: In general usage , an essential part of a thing surrounded by other essential things.

subdefinitions.definition: The central part of a fruit , containing the kernels or seeds .
examples: the core of an apple or quince

subdefinitions.definition: The heart or inner part of a physical thing.
The anatomical core , muscles which bridge abdomen and thorax .
The center or inner part of a space or area .

definitions.definition: The most important part of a thing or aggregate of things wherever located and whether of any determinate location at all; the essence .

subdefinitions.definition: A technical term for classification of things denoting those parts of a category that are most easily or most likely understood as within it. ( botany ) The main and most diverse monophyletic group within a clade or taxonomic group. ( game theory ) The set of feasible allocations that cannot be improved upon by a subset (a coalition ) of the economy 's agents .
( art ) A thematic aesthetic ; objects related to a specific topic
examples: Photographs of cottage core focuses on countrysides or forests.

definitions.definition: particular parts of technical instruments or machines essential in function:

subdefinitions.definition: ( engineering , manufacturing ) The portion of a mold that creates a cavity or impression within the part ( casting or molded part) or that makes a hole in or through the part.
( computing , informal , historical ) Ellipsis of core memory ( “ magnetic data storage ” ) .

( computer hardware ) An individual computer processor , in the sense when several processors (called cores or CPU cores ) are plugged together in one single integrated circuit to work as one (called a multi-core processor).
examples: I wanted to play a particular computer game, which required I buy a new computer, so while the game said it needed at least a dual- core processor, I wanted my computer to be a bit ahead of the curve, so I bought a quad- core .

subdefinitions.definition: ( engineering ) The material between surface materials in a structured composite sandwich material.
examples: a floor panel with a Nomex honeycomb core

subdefinitions.definition: ( engineering , nuclear physics ) The inner part of a nuclear reactor , in which the nuclear reaction takes place.
( military ) The central fissile portion of a fission weapon .
examples: In a hollow- core design, neutrons escape from the core more readily, allowing more fissile material to be used (and thus allowing for a greater yield) while still keeping the core subcritical prior to detonation.

subdefinitions.definition: A piece of ferromagnetic material (e.g., soft iron ), inside the windings of an electromagnet , that channels the magnetic field .
( printing ) A hollow cylindrical piece of cardboard around which a web of paper or plastic is wound .

definitions.definition: Hence particular parts of a subject studied or examined by technical operations, likened by position and practical or structural robustness to kernels , cores in the most vulgar sense above.

subdefinitions.definition: ( medicine ) A tiny sample of organic material obtained by means of a fine-needle biopsy .
The bony process which forms the central axis of the horns in many animals.
A disorder of sheep caused by worms in the liver .
( biochemistry ) The central part of a protein 's structure, consisting mostly of hydrophobic amino acids .
A cylindrical sample of rock or other materials obtained by core drilling.
( physics ) An atomic nucleus plus inner electrons (i.e., an atom , except for its valence electrons ).

main_definition: In general usage , an essential part of a thing surrounded by other essential things.
secondary_definitions: The most important part of a thing or aggregate of things wherever located and whether of any determinate location at all; the essence .

definitions.definition: ( obsolete ) A body of individuals; an assemblage .

main_definition: ( obsolete ) A body of individuals; an assemblage .

definitions.definition: A miner's underground working time or shift .

main_definition: A miner's underground working time or shift .

definitions.definition: ( historical units of measure ) Alternative form of cor : a former Hebrew and Phoenician unit of volume .

main_definition: ( historical units of measure ) Alternative form of cor : a former Hebrew and Phoenician unit of volume .

definitions.definition: ( automotive , machinery , aviation , marine ) A deposit paid by the purchaser of a rebuilt part, to be refunded on return of a used, rebuildable part, or the returned rebuildable part itself.

main_definition: ( automotive , machinery , aviation , marine ) A deposit paid by the purchaser of a rebuilt part, to be refunded on return of a used, rebuildable part, or the returned rebuildable part itself.

definitions.definition: An aesthetic ending in the suffix -core , such as cottagecore , normcore , etc.

main_definition: ( neologism ) An aesthetic ending in the suffix -core , such as cottagecore , normcore , etc.
